      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SAN SEBASTIAN (4) has been good from wide barriers in the last two outings at Newcastle, working forward to lead when scoring by 5.7m two back then finishing only 1.2m away as runner-up last week. A lower draw could see him tough to stop. MAJOR ICON NZ (1) has been solid in finishing midfield from back row draws in his last two outings. Led to win at this circuit and distance last month so has the speed to take advantage of the ace draw. DUTY OF CARE (8) was tough in racing parked but fighting well for a last-start win by 2 metres at this circuit and distance. Draws on the back row but can make an impact again with even luck. RICK REILLY NZ (7) could be close to a win after placing in two of his last three starts at Newcastle. Draws for a trail and is a player if he gets the gaps.",
